args: I beg your pardon, Elisanne, but...\nWell, if you are not busy, might you care\nto join me for a game of volleyball?
I'm not familiar with that particular game.
Volleyball is actually a rather\npopular beach activity.
It is a simple game where two teams\ntry to hit a ball into the other's court.
With the conditions being that you cannot\nhold the ball or let it fall on the sand.
I see. That does sounds like fun.\nIf you're sure I would be an adequate\nchoice, I would love to try it.
Uh, I mean, of COURSE it will be fun!\nIt was my idea, after all.
Well, it looks like this all worked out.\nHow about I keep score?
Gettin' a game of volleyball going, eh?\nCount me in—I'm a spike MACHINE!
What?! Er, I mean...that's fine, Luca,\nbut we need an even number of players.
Looks like I've just been drafted.\nYou mind keeping score, Notte?
You betcha! Who's on what team?
Dunno. Guess we could draw straws?
We are NOT drawing straws!\nElly and I will be a team, and that's...
Uh... I mean... *ahem*\nMy apologies. I had a bit of\nsand caught in my throat there.
I believe Elisanne would be most\ncomfortable teaming up with a fellow\nPaladyn. ...Which would be me.
For what is sport, but battle in miniature?\nThis is a perfect opportunity to practice\ncooperative combat tactics!
Therefore it only makes sense that we\nPaladyns should be on the same team.
I suppose that does make\na certain amount of sense.
Are you sure about this, Julietta?
No, it's just... You're not going to panic\nand get a stomachache or something?
Ah, yes. That. ...Er, but I also don't think\nI could ever face Elly as an opponent!
Hey, enough with the hushed whisperin'!\nPick teams already and let's get this\nshow on the damn road!
Okay, Luca, looks like it's you and me.
Then Julietta and I will be the other team.\nIt is a pleasure, Julietta.
The pleasure is all mine. Let us show\nthem what we Paladyns are capable of!
I don't have a whistle here, so...\nTWEEEET! Game on!
Volleyball is all about teamwork.\nIf you set me up, I will do the rest.
Your victory was all but assured\nthe moment I joined your team!
Your confidence is certainly inspiring.\nI shall give my all, but put my faith in\nyour skills to carry the day.
(Elly is putting her faith in me?!\nAugh! S-such pressure! Owwww...)
(N-no! This is no time to be\ngetting a stomachache!)
(Uh oh. Julietta is really cringing.\nLooks like a stomachache coming on.)
I'd better go easy on them with this\nfirst serve. ...Hah.
What the hell?! I've never SEEN\na return like that before!
That's one point for Team Paladyn,\nand NO points for Team Chump!
What did I tell you, Your Highness?\nSports are battles in miniature!
And while I appreciate your concern,\nI will not stand for you giving anything\nless than your finest effort on this court.
Judging by what you just did,\nI don't think I needed to bother.
Hey, step it up, {player_name}!\nI ain't gonna lose this match!
Let us see if you can handle this serve...\nHAAAAAAAAH!
Another point for Team Paladyn,\nand more shame for Team Chump!
This is mere child's play to me.
All right, my turn to serve. Taaake...THIS!
She just slammed it right back!\nDamn it, I gotta try that again!

That's game, set, aaaaaand match!
Elisanne and Julietta win my praise,
while Team Chump will be booed
until my throat is sore! Boooooo!
You won the day for us, Julietta.\nYou have my thanks.
Heh. You needn't thank me for that.\nI barely broke a sweat.
*pant* *heave*  Should've known better...\nthan to go up against Paladyns...
Yeah... Especially Julietta...\nShe's a one-woman wreckin' crew!
Well, yeah! I mean, you just did\npretty much everything over there.
It's sorta amazing how you were able\nto cover the entire court by yourself.
Er, Elisanne? You DID get a chance\nto handle the ball there, yes?
No, the opportunity did not really present\nitself—but it is hard to shine when paired\nwith a true veteran like yourself!
A THOUSAND apologies, Elisanne!\nThat was the basest form of ball hoggery!
I am very confused right now.
She probably thinks she ruined the game\nfor you by monopolizing the ball.
Oh, but I don't care about that one whit!\nJulietta, come back! ...Julietta?
